N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 4066.2 - Fields, enclosures defined

State Regulations

In artificially constructed steeplechase courses and in
hurdle races, the spaces between the fences or hurdles and the space between
the last fence and the finish, are considered as fields or enclosures for the
purpose of this Part. Notes
